        },
        {
            "id": 1,
            "parent": 0,
            "text": "We describe an explicit mechanism for the emergence of a dynamical holographic bulk from the structure of entanglement in a quantum state . <S>",
            "relation": "ROOT"
        },
        {
            "id": 2,
            "parent": 1,
            "text": "We start with a generic system in complete isolation ,",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 3,
            "parent": 4,
            "text": "assuming",
            "relation": "ATTRIBUTION"
        },
        {
            "id": 4,
            "parent": 2,
            "text": "it has a classical limit",
            "relation": "CONDITION"
        },
        {
            "id": 5,
            "parent": 4,
            "text": "involving coherent states . <S>",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 6,
            "parent": 2,
            "text": "Then we entangle it with another system of that kind ,",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 7,
            "parent": 6,
            "text": "and subject the pair to a decohering process . <S>",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 8,
            "parent": 2,
            "text": "We make a number of broadly applicable and physically reasonable assumptions about this setup . <S>",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 9,
            "parent": 10,
            "text": "First , we assume",
            "relation": "ATTRIBUTION"
        },
        {
            "id": 10,
            "parent": 8,
            "text": "that the states selected by the decoherence",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 11,
            "parent": 10,
            "text": "( called pointer states )",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 12,
            "parent": 10,
            "text": "have the same local symmetries as the isolated systems , in a sense",
            "relation": "SAME-UNIT"
        },
        {
            "id": 13,
            "parent": 12,
            "text": "which is made precise . <S>",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 14,
            "parent": 15,
            "text": "We also assume",
            "relation": "ATTRIBUTION"
        },
        {
            "id": 15,
            "parent": 10,
            "text": "that the modular Hamiltonians of pointer states scale inversely with Planck 's constant ,",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 16,
            "parent": 15,
            "text": "so that the pointer states are highly entangled in the classical limit . <S>",
            "relation": "ENABLEMENT"
        },
        {
            "id": 17,
            "parent": 15,
            "text": "Finally , we require the timescale of decoherence",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 18,
            "parent": 17,
            "text": "to scale in a certain way with Planck 's constant ,",
            "relation": "ENABLEMENT"
        },
        {
            "id": 19,
            "parent": 17,
            "text": "so that decoherence happens very frequently in the classical limit , but not too frequently . <S>",
            "relation": "ENABLEMENT"
        },
        {
            "id": 20,
            "parent": 21,
            "text": "Given these assumptions ,",
            "relation": "CONDITION"
        },
        {
            "id": 21,
            "parent": 22,
            "text": "we demonstrate",
            "relation": "ATTRIBUTION"
        },
        {
            "id": 22,
            "parent": 1,
            "text": "that the semiclassical evolution of the system is dominated by a certain dynamical generalisation of Uhlmann holonomy . <S>",
            "relation": "FINDINGS"
        },
        {
            "id": 23,
            "parent": 22,
            "text": "We construct a coherent state path integral for this evolution ,",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 24,
            "parent": 25,
            "text": "showing",
            "relation": "ATTRIBUTION"
        },
        {
            "id": 25,
            "parent": 23,
            "text": "that the semiclassical fields evolve in a spacetime with one more dimension than the isolated case . <S>",
            "relation": "CAUSE-RESULT"
        },
        {
            "id": 26,
            "parent": 25,
            "text": "The additional dimension is generated by modular flow . <S> <P>",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        }
